
                       ##### Instance initialization blocks #####

* Instance initialization blocks become part of the constructor and execute after the super() 
statement at object creation.

Can we inherit instance blocks from super class to child class in Java?:-
* Instance initialization blocks become part of the constructor and execute after the super() statement 
at object creation. As constructors cannot be inherited and can be accessed only through 
super() which is already the first statement in any constructor it dose not make sense to make 
it participate in inheritance(the creators of java were smart enough :) )